, last-presented, hebbian-boost, learned-weight, calibration-count) is the prerequisite for all learned behavior. Implementation sequence: ATT-0 schema → ATT-1 session-aware surprisal → ATT-2 Hebbian feedback → ATT-3 task-conditioned relevance → ATT-4 wire into ACP rendering. Total estimated: ~14 hours of focused implementation. DEPENDENCIES: ATT-0 depends on nothing. ATT-1..4 depend on ATT-0 linearly. ATT-5..7 (Bayesian calibration, decay rate learning, meta-calibration) depend on HL-3/4 (hypothesis outcomes). SPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-024, INV-ATTENTION-001..006. VERIFICATION: After ATT-4, ACP output should vary across sessions based on presentation history. Metric: 'productive action rate after presentation' should improve vs static baseline.; Session entity: :recon/trace-837792966e84d8bc; Session entity: :task/t-eca0977f; Session entity: :recon/trace-7234637a8fa3162a; Session entity: :recon/trace-eff77b40d723aa58; Session entity: :recon/trace-99028f1ccc18ccb7; Session entity: :recon/trace-42ee70aaa52fa240; Session entity: :recon/trace-64be820539c3c10c; Session entity: :recon/trace-4eced142370b61c4; Session entity: :recon/trace-b20d9d1b9edb9f0d; Session entity: :task/t-065fdbaa; Session entity: :recon/trace-e5437b4141033520; Session entity: :recon/trace-3390da9c4659c8ef; Session entity: :recon/trace-0fbd92777864efa2; Session entity: :recon/trace-b727a0a8b5f3a8e2; Session entity: :recon/trace-0a5a942dd3e97d46; AUDIT-036 FINDING 5: GUIDANCE.RS GOD MODULE. guidance.rs is 11,476 LOC — 15% of the entire kernel in one file. It handles 6 distinct responsibilities: (1) M(t) methodology score computation, (2) R(t) routing/impact calculation, (3) ACP context block rendering, (4) footer generation and injection, (5) methodology gap detection, (6) surprisal scoring and attention weight management. This creates coupling: any change to ACP rendering potentially affects M(t) computation, R(t) routing, and footer generation simultaneously. Every module in the kernel depends on guidance.rs for at least one function. PROPOSED SPLIT: (A) methodology.rs — M(t), gap detection, methodology scoring (~3K LOC), (B) routing.rs — R(t), impact, surprisal, acquisition function (~4K LOC), (C) context.rs — ACP blocks, rendering, footer, budget interaction (~4K LOC). VERIFICATION: After split, each module should have <5K LOC, compile independently, and pass existing tests without modification. No public API change — just internal reorganization. RISK: Low. The split is mechanical. No logic changes. TIMING: Should happen before Phase D attention work deepens, since ATT-0..4 all add to guidance.rs. SPEC: INV-GUIDANCE-001 through INV-GUIDANCE-011 are the invariants under test.; Session entity: :task/t-5d95c2ef; Session entity: :recon/trace-a6705605c47cb10f; Session entity: :witness/fbw.46e5228afb8ae4f2; Session entity: :recon/trace-019ce9479a204aa7; Session entity: :recon/trace-99b0bad52a79fa62; Session entity: :recon/trace-7f79ddcfc9eb236f; AUDIT-036 FINDING 9: THE REAL ARCHITECTURE (MARKOV BLANKET INSIGHT). The project has converged on something deeper than a CLI tool. Braid is a learned boundary (Markov blanket) between two epistemological systems: the formal store (append-only, datom-based) and the statistical LLM (attention-based, mortal). The attention mechanism A(t) decides what crosses that boundary. The 5-layer stack: (1) Substrate (Store+Query+Schema+Merge+Resolution) = the formal side, (2) Lifecycle (Harvest+Seed+Session+Guidance) = the operating system, (3) Intelligence (CE+COTX+Budget+ACP+Topology+R(t)) = the emergent layer, (4) Self-Calibration (Hypothesis Ledger+Comonadic Depth+Attention+Policy Calibration) = learning about learning, (5) Active Runtime (Daemon+Observer+MCP+External) = autonomy. Each layer depends on all layers below. Phase D (current) is Layer 4. Phase E (next major) is Layer 5. SPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-024 (Learned Attention as Markov Blanket), C8 (substrate independence). VERIFICATION: Every feature should be classifiable into exactly one layer. Features spanning two layers indicate a decomposition failure.; Session entity: :recon/trace-2fa70928334a92f3; Session entity: :recon/trace-ff60bb61f97b421b; Session entity: :recon/trace-6b59e4fa46a35cbc; Session entity: :witness/fbw.b26dd8970de90f98; Session entity: :recon/trace-cb0fd07c0b4177d0; Session entity: :recon/trace-a825fe2bae1d034d; Session entity: :recon/trace-b93d7aa2a4bcdc52; Session entity: :task/t-39fbcc01; Session entity: :recon/trace-9d6ba8503fb60b05; Session entity: :recon/trace-7ad80f1409f0c340; Session entity: :recon/trace-4abaf6c25c04da79; AUDIT-036 FINDING 4: HYPOTHESIS LEDGER IS THE MOST IMPORTANT OPEN LOOP. 24 predictions recorded, 0 completed, mean error 0.000 (no data), trend 'insufficient data'. The self-calibrating acquisition function A(t) cannot improve without outcome data. The predictions reference tasks t-4f9b504c, t-6ae5d230, t-5c3db83f which are all still open. HL-3 (outcome matching on task close) is implemented. HL-4 (calibration metrics in status) is implemented. But the loop has never fired because no predicted task has been closed since predictions started being recorded. This is the system's single most important feedback mechanism — without it, R(t) routing weights are static guesses, attention scores can't calibrate, and the entire 'self-calibrating epistemology' thesis remains unverified. FIRST ACTION: Close one of the three predicted tasks, then verify: (1) HL-3 fires and records actual ΔF(S), (2) HL-4 updates mean error and trend, (3) braid status shows non-zero calibration data. SPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-018 (Hypothesis Ledger), INV-FOUNDATION-008. DEPENDENCIES: None — this is pure administrative action on existing code.; AUDIT-036 DETAIL: GUIDANCE MODULE SPLIT PLAN. guidance.rs (11,476 LOC) → three modules. DECOMPOSITION: (A) methodology.rs (~3,500 LOC) — Functions: methodology_score(), methodology_gaps(), compute_methodology_health(), session_methodology_summary(). Data: MethodologyScore, MethodologyGap, MethodologyHealth. Invariants: INV-GUIDANCE-001..005. (B) routing.rs (~4,000 LOC) — Functions: compute_routing(), compute_impact(), compute_surprisal(), spec_anchor_factor(), contextual_observation_factor(). Data: RoutingScore, ImpactFactors, SurprisalMetrics. Invariants: INV-GUIDANCE-006..011, INV-GUIDANCE-017, INV-GUIDANCE-024..025. (C) context.rs (~4,000 LOC) — Functions: build_status_projection(), build_verbose(), build_seed_context(), render_footer(), pyramid_compress(). Data: ContextBlock, AttentionScore, GuidanceContext. Invariants: INV-BUDGET-001..006. MIGRATION: (1) Create three new files. (2) Move functions + types. (3) Re-export from guidance.rs (or new guidance/mod.rs). (4) All existing tests pass without modification. (5) No public API change — lib.rs exports stay identical. RISK: Mechanical refactor, no logic changes. Could be done by subagents in parallel (one file each). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs → crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance/{mod.rs,methodology.rs,routing.rs,context.rs}; Session entity: :recon/trace-acf94fd84154c309; Session entity: :recon/trace-08fd3b4a3d7487d3; Session entity: :recon/trace-278418ff5ab4853e; Session entity: :recon/trace-d2b6e7976a17fe0a; Session entity: :task/t-879f6caf; Session entity: :recon/trace-15e89bfea3251eb4; Session entity: :recon/trace-3d262bdf3ee5237b; Session entity: :recon/trace-829dfcdb5c288df9; Session entity: :recon/trace-036b0bd2c416518a; Session entity: :recon/trace-a01874277409557d; Session entity: :task/t-3cf8907b; Session entity: :recon/trace-2ec704d801c3654b; Session entity: :recon/trace-18295940120864f1; Session entity: :recon/trace-ba8eaa8942fb0182; Session entity: :recon/trace-d6dd575f1c93c04b; Session entity: :recon/trace-19e8c39dec706aaf; AUDIT-036 FINDING 1: ROADMAP FALSIFICATION. The SEED.md 5-stage roadmap (Stage 0-4) has been falsified by the actual project trajectory. The stages assumed linear progression: CLI → multi-agent. The actual trajectory was: CLI → formal epistemology → self-calibrating attention mechanism. Evidence: (1) Stage 1 defined 'budget-aware output' but the project discovered learned attention (ADR-024), making static budgets a subset. (2) Stage 2 defined 'branching + deliberation' but deliberation was implemented as part of Phase C intelligence, not as a separate stage. (3) Stage 3 defined 'multi-agent coordination' but topology (3K LOC, 75 tests) was built and has never been used with real agents. (4) Stage 4 defined 'advanced intelligence' but the hypothesis ledger, comonadic depth, and attention mechanism emerged from dog-fooding, not from the stage plan. The 5-phase model (Substrate/Lifecycle/Intelligence/Self-Calibration/Active Runtime) better describes both what was built and what remains. VERIFICATION: Compare deliverables per stage vs deliverables per phase. Every completed artifact maps to a phase; many stage boundaries are crossed or irrelevant. IMPACT: Misaligned roadmap causes task inflation (tasks created for stage milestones that don't match actual work), misleading progress percentages (Stage 1 '85%' by original definition, 30% by current understanding), and wasted planning effort.; Session entity: :recon/trace-747ccbc3afadb073; Session entity: :recon/trace-0085174756cca8fd; Session entity: :task/t-02889f05; Session entity: :recon/trace-a3f704b12fe18bd1; Session entity: :recon/trace-3db3d69e3b59eda0; Session entity: :recon/trace-8ff3906abdded866; Session entity: :recon/trace-eb45d752c65cd771; AUDIT-036 DETAIL: RESOLUTION PROPTEST GAP. Resolution module (1,341 LOC) has 23 unit tests but lacks property-based tests for the critical commutativity invariant. The resolution modes (LWW, Lattice, MultiValue) each claim commutativity: resolve(a, b) == resolve(b, a). This is tested in Stateright for merge-level operations but NOT tested at the resolution function level with arbitrary inputs. A proptest strategy should generate: (1) Random attribute with random resolution mode, (2) Two conflicting values, (3) Verify resolve(v1, v2) == resolve(v2, v1) for all modes. ADDITIONAL PROPERTY: Resolution should be idempotent — resolve(resolve(a, b), b) == resolve(a, b). And associative for lattice mode — resolve(resolve(a, b), c) == resolve(a, resolve(b, c)). SPEC: INV-RESOLUTION-001 (commutativity), INV-RESOLUTION-002 (determinism). ACCEPTANCE: 1000 proptest cases pass for each property. No counterexample found.; Session entity: :recon/trace-6bbec2f908bc4afd; Session entity: :recon/trace-6b6efdb8b3235aa9; Session entity: :task/t-99bde422; AUDIT-036 FINDING 3: TASK INFLATION. 328 open tasks, 136 'likely implemented' but not closed. 46 open EPICs (only 3 closed). The task system has become a burden rather than a tool. ROOT CAUSES: (1) Tasks are created speculatively during crystallization/observation — every observe/harvest creates candidate tasks. (2) EPICs are created for conceptual clusters but never systematically closed when their constituent tasks complete. (3) The audit function identifies likely-done tasks but doesn't auto-close them. (4) Many EPICs describe Phase E work (daemon, active observer, MCP extraction) that won't be needed for months. IMPACT: R(t) acquisition function is diluted across 328 candidates. The routing impact score spreads thin — top recommendation has impact=0.27 where ideal would be >0.5 for clear prioritization. Every session spends cognitive budget reading task lists instead of doing work. VERIFICATION: After closing 136 likely-done tasks + triaging EPICs to <80 open / <10 EPICs, R(t) top recommendation impact should increase to >0.40. SOLUTION: Batch close, EPIC triage, institute task decay (untouched 5+ sessions → P4).; AUDIT-036 DETAIL: BATCH WITNESS AUTOMATION. The 238 INVs lacking L2+ witness need automated witnessing. Current state: braid witness check verifies individual INV↔test alignment. braid trace --commit scans code for INV/ADR/NEG references. The gap is connecting them: many INVs have corresponding tests (via trace scan) but the witness record hasn't been created/promoted to L2. APPROACH: (1) braid witness auto-promote — for each INV with a trace-linked test function, auto-create a witness record at depth L2 (test-verified). (2) For INVs WITHOUT trace-linked tests, output a list of 'unwitnessed INVs' for manual attention. (3) Expected result: 238 → ~50 unwitnessed (the rest have tests but no formal witness record). SPEC: INV-WITNESS-011 (every current-stage INV must have L2+ FBW). DEPENDENCIES: braid trace --commit must be current (currently stale — 32 files modified). ACCEPTANCE: After auto-promote, braid witness completeness shows >80% coverage. F(S) boundary for spec↔impl should improve from 0.82 to >0.90.; Session entity: :recon/trace-c01a09febb724d8b; Session entity: :recon/trace-b3a97ae85f47998c; Session entity: :task/t-84448be7; Session entity: :recon/trace-4fe7d797a935cc1f; Session entity: :recon/trace-7a5d08d26f9d8d35; Session entity: :recon/trace-40e2af63e93ea7f2; Session entity: :task/t-90ebb265; Session entity: :recon/trace-daa2db843edce47e; Session entity: :recon/trace-c3dfd4108e8bb0fa; Session entity: :recon/trace-6ccaaac6ba7aa833; Session entity: :recon/trace-198d2b928668e87b; Session entity: :recon/trace-26b53927e200f0e1; Session entity: :recon/trace-656ff099932c2196; Session entity: :recon/trace-641d7b8810c34650; Session entity: :task/t-0d64b828; Session entity: :recon/trace-3aac5b415ebe2b43; Session entity: :recon/trace-148bd293bbbd2e58; Session entity: :recon/trace-0b20fce08cf0fa67; Session entity: :task/t-9fc8fb9e; Session entity: :recon/trace-eec3a09f248a6a94; Session entity: :recon/trace-11d7df2671654289; Session entity: :recon/trace-83325cc7e695439d; Session entity: :witness/fbw.a87acf345804c206; Session entity: :witness/fbw.f60f95c1f9794196; Session entity: :task/t-32da0ff5; Session entity: :recon/trace-dfe901c65f4b9837\nSession entity: :impl/braid.src.commands.init.adr-foundation-013; Session entity: :impl/braid-kernel.src.policy.neg-foundation-003; Session entity: :impl/braid-kern